headline.main: 1942 SAW ECLIPSE OF AXIS IN AFRICA; Allies Turned Ebb of Defeat at El Alamein Into Tide of Sweeping Victory AVIATION HAD VITAL ROLE Survey Shows That Persistent Strafing Softened Up Foe, Strangled Reinforcements

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt Dec. 31 (Delayed) -- The old year of 1942 ended today like all other years of the African war, with the Allies apparently victorious, but, unlike other years, 1942 appears to have left the Axis no chance of staging a comeback on this continent.
abstract: '42 seen as eclipse of Axis in Africa; US air role held vital factor
